Step 1
Customer selects a product.

Example:
Laptop = ₹50,000

↓

Step 2
Customer proceeds to Checkout.

↓

Step 3
Customer selects
Credit/Debit Card

↓

Step 4
Customer enters
• Card Number
• Expiry Date
• CVV
• Card Holder Name

↓

Step 5
Customer clicks
"Place Order"

↓

Step 6
Merchant website/plugin sends an API request to the Novalnet server.

The request contains:
• Merchant ID
• Authentication Signature
• Amount
• Currency
• Order Number
• Customer Details
• Billing Address
• Payment Type
• Card Token/Card Data
• Callback URL
• Other required parameters

↓

Step 7
Novalnet receives the API request.

↓

Step 8
Novalnet validates the basic request.

Checks include:
• Merchant ID is valid.
• Signature/Auth token is valid.
• Required parameters are present.
• Amount is valid.
• Currency is supported.
• Payment method is enabled.
• Request format is correct.

If any check fails → API returns an error.

↓

Step 9
Novalnet generates a unique Transaction ID (TID).

Example:
TID = 325874612398

↓

Step 10
Novalnet performs fraud and risk checks.

Examples:
• BIN Country Check
• IP Country Check
• Address Verification
• Velocity Check
• Blacklist Check
• Email Validation
• Device Fingerprinting
• Card Expiry Check
• CVV Check
• 3D Secure Decision
• Customer Risk Score

If risk is high:
→ Decline or send for 3D Secure/manual review.

↓

Step 11
If risk checks pass,
Novalnet forwards the authorization request to the Acquirer.

↓

Step 12
Acquirer performs its own validations.

Examples:
• Merchant account active
• Merchant allowed to accept this card
• Transaction amount limits
• Card network available
• Compliance checks

↓

Step 13
Acquirer forwards the request to the Card Network.

Example:
Visa or Mastercard

↓

Step 14
Card Network identifies the correct Issuing Bank using the card BIN and routes the transaction.

↓

Step 15
Issuing Bank performs authorization checks.

Examples:
• Card exists
• Card is active
• Card not expired
• CVV correct
• Sufficient balance/credit limit
• Card not blocked
• Fraud monitoring
• Daily transaction limit
• OTP / 3D Secure authentication (if required)

↓

Step 16
Issuing Bank sends the result.

Approved
or
Declined

↓

Step 17
Card Network forwards the response to the Acquirer.

↓

Step 18
Acquirer forwards the response to Novalnet.

↓

Step 19
Novalnet updates the transaction status.

Examples:
• SUCCESS
• FAILURE
• PENDING
• ON HOLD

↓

Step 20
Novalnet sends the API response back to the Merchant.

The response contains:
• Transaction Status
• TID
• Authorization Code
• Payment Result
• Response Code
• Response Message

↓

Step 21
Merchant updates the order.

If Approved:
• Order = Confirmed
• Stock reduced
• Confirmation email sent
• Product shipped

If Declined:
• Order = Failed
• Customer sees the error message

↓

Step 22
Settlement (after authorization)

Issuing Bank
→ Card Network
→ Acquirer
→ Novalnet (if applicable)
→ Merchant Bank Account

Money is transferred according to the settlement cycle (e.g., T+1, T+2).
invoice:
Step 1
Customer selects a product.

↓

Step 2
Customer goes to Checkout.

↓

Step 3
Customer selects
Invoice Payment (Buy Now, Pay Later)

↓

Step 4
Customer enters billing details.

↓

Step 5
Customer clicks
"Place Order"

↓

Step 6
Merchant sends an API request to Novalnet.

Request contains:
• Merchant ID
• Authentication Signature
• Amount
• Currency
• Customer Details
• Billing Address
• Order Number
• Payment Type = Invoice

↓

Step 7
Novalnet receives the request.

↓

Step 8
Novalnet validates basic parameters.

Checks:
• Merchant authentication
• Required parameters
• Payment method enabled
• Amount & currency
• Customer details

↓

Step 9
Novalnet generates a unique TID.

↓

Step 10
Novalnet performs invoice risk checks.

Examples:
• Creditworthiness check
• Address verification
• Identity verification
• Blacklist check
• Fraud detection
• Duplicate transaction check
• Order amount limits
• Country eligibility

If risk is high:
→ Decline or put the transaction On Hold.

↓

Step 11
If approved,
Novalnet creates the invoice payment transaction.

↓

Step 12
Novalnet returns a successful API response.

Response includes:
• TID
• Payment Status
• Invoice Number (if applicable)
• Bank Account Details
• Payment Reference
• Due Date

↓

Step 13
Merchant confirms the order.

↓

Step 14
Merchant ships the product.

↓

Step 15
Customer receives the invoice.

↓

Step 16
Customer pays the invoice before the due date.

↓

Step 17
Novalnet receives the payment,
matches it using the payment reference,
and updates the transaction.

↓

Step 18
Merchant receives the money.
