direct sepa:
Step 1
Customer selects a product.

↓

Step 2
Checkout page.

↓

Step 3
Customer selects
SEPA Direct Debit.

↓

Step 4
Customer enters:
• IBAN
• Account Holder Name

↓

Step 5
Customer accepts the SEPA Mandate
(authorizes the merchant to debit the account).

↓

Step 6
Customer clicks
"Place Order"

↓

Step 7
Merchant sends API request to Novalnet.

Request contains:
• Merchant ID
• Amount
• Currency
• Customer Details
• IBAN
• Mandate Information
• Payment Type = SEPA Direct Debit

↓

Step 8
Novalnet validates:
• Merchant authentication
• Required parameters
• IBAN format
• Country support
• Payment method
• Amount

↓

Step 9
Novalnet generates a TID.

↓

Step 10
Novalnet performs SEPA risk checks.

Examples:
• IBAN validation
• Blacklist check
• Duplicate transaction check
• Fraud detection
• Customer verification
• Country eligibility

↓

Step 11
Novalnet creates the SEPA Direct Debit transaction.

↓

Step 12
Novalnet submits the debit request through the banking network.

↓

Step 13
Customer's bank checks:
• IBAN exists
• Account is active
• Sufficient funds
• Valid SEPA mandate
• No debit restrictions

↓

Step 14
Customer's bank:
• Approves → Amount is debited.
OR
• Rejects → Payment fails (e.g., insufficient funds, invalid account, revoked mandate).

↓

Step 15
Novalnet receives the bank response.

↓

Step 16
Novalnet updates the transaction status.

• SUCCESS
• PENDING
• FAILED

↓

Step 17
Merchant receives the API/callback notification.

↓

Step 18
If successful,
Merchant confirms the order and ships the product.

charge back:
Step 1
Customer makes a card payment.

↓

Step 2
Merchant receives the payment and ships the product.

↓

Step 3
Customer disputes the transaction.

Reasons:
• Unauthorized transaction
• Product not received
• Product defective
• Duplicate charge
• Fraud

↓

Step 4
Customer contacts the Issuing Bank.

↓

Step 5
Issuing Bank reviews the complaint.

↓

Step 6
Issuing Bank sends a chargeback request through the Card Network (Visa/Mastercard).

↓

Step 7
Card Network forwards the chargeback to the Acquirer.

↓

Step 8
Acquirer informs Novalnet and the Merchant.

↓

Step 9
Merchant provides evidence.

Examples:
• Delivery proof
• Invoice
• Tracking number
• Customer communication
• Signed receipt

↓

Step 10
Decision

If merchant wins:
→ Chargeback is reversed and the merchant keeps the money.

If customer wins:
→ Money is returned to the customer, and the merchant loses the payment (and may also pay a chargeback fee).
